<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Talk about a close call. </p>

<p>A person looking for their cat outside of their California home was shocked to discover a mountain lion scoping out some kids riding their bike nearby. </p>

<p>The brief clip, filmed in Pacifica on September 19, shows the large predator watching the kids from behind the camera person's first yard gate. </p>

<p>A person looking for their cat was shocked to discover a large mountain lion watching children ride their bikes from a yard in Pacifica, California</p>

<p>It stares at the kids before noticing the camera person, who screamed at the children and told them to run inside. </p>

<p>It runs toward the camera before making a quick turn, jumping over the fence and hiding under a nearby truck. </p>

<p>The September 19 clip shows the large feline watching the bikers before it was shooed off by the camera person</p>

<p>After the camera person screams, the mountain lion runs toward them before jumping over the side fence</p>

<p>The clip ends showing the large feline hiding under the vehicle as the kids hurry to get inside.</p>

<p>The camera person shared in the video caption that the mountain lion was chased 'off into the side yard and back hill.' </p>

<p>The cat-lover's own little kitty did eventually come back home a 'few hours later.'  </p>

<p>The large feline hides under a truck and watches the kids before it is scared off </p>
